<div class="grid-row">
  <div class="column-two-thirds">
    <div class="pub-c-title">
      <h1 class="pub-c-title__text pub-c-title__text--long">
        Get a divorce: step by step
      </h1>
    </div>

    <p class="pub-c-lead-paragraph">
      Find out how to legally end your marriage in England and Wales.
    </p>

    <div class="task-list task-list--large js-hidden" data-module="tasklistnew">
      <ol class="task-list__list">
        <li class="task-list__group">
          <span class="task-list__number">
            <span class="visuallyhidden">Step</span> 1
          </span>

          <div class="task-list__step js-step">
            <div class="task-list__header js-toggle-panel">
              <h2 class="task-list__title js-step-title">
                Check if you can get divorced
              </h2>
            </div>

            <div class="task-list__panel js-panel">
              <p>Your marriage must meet certain legal requirements in order for you to be able to get a divorce.</p>
              <ul class="task-list__panel-links--required">
                <li>
                  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/divorce">Check your marriage meets the criteria</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/divorce/grounds-for-divorce">Check the list of reasons why you can get a divorce</a>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="task-list__group">
          <span class="task-list__number">
            <span class="visuallyhidden">Step</span> 2
          </span>

          <div class="task-list__step task-list__step--optional js-step">
            <div class="task-list__header js-toggle-panel">
              <h2 class="task-list__title js-step-title">
                Make arrangements for your children, money and property
              </h2>
            </div>

            <div class="task-list__panel js-panel">
              <p>You should try and agree how you'll deal with your children, money and property before you start your divorce.</p>
              <ul class="task-list__panel-links--required">
                <li>
                  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/looking-after-children-divorce">Make arrangements for your children</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/money-property-when-relationship-ends">Divide your money and property</a>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="task-list__group">
          <span class="task-list__number">
            <span class="visuallyhidden">Step</span> 3
          </span>

          <div class="task-list__step js-step">
            <div class="task-list__header js-toggle-panel">
              <h2 class="task-list__title js-step-title">
                File for divorce
              </h2>
            </div>

            <div class="task-list__panel js-panel">
              <p>You need to fill in a divorce petition form. The court will send a copy to your husband or wife.</p>
              <ul class="task-list__panel-links--required">
                <li>
                  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/divorce/file-for-divorce">How to start the divorce process</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=1115">Fill in the divorce petition form</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/divorce/file-for-divorce">Pay the fee</a> <span class="task-list__cost">&pound;550</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/get-help-with-court-fees">Get help with court fees</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="https://courttribunalfinder.service.gov.uk/search/postcode?aol=Divorce&amp;spoe=start">Send copies of the form to your nearest divorce centre</a>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p>The court will tell you when your husband or wife responds and what you'll need to do next.</p>

              <div class="task-list__inner-step task-list__inner-step--optional">
                <p>If you don't know your husband or wife's address, you need to try to find it so the court can send them the divorce petition.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://www.gov.uk/divorce-missing-husband-wife">Try to find your husband or wife's address</a>
                    <span class="task-list__cost">&pound;0 to &pound;100</span>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=1112">Apply to skip the divorce petition if you can't find their address</a>
                    <span class="task-list__cost">&pound;50</span>
                  </li>
                </ul>

                <p>If your husband or wife can't make decisions by themselves, someone needs to respond to the divorce petition.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://www.gov.uk/divorce/if-your-husband-or-wife-lacks-mental-capacity">Check they have someone to act on their behalf</a>
                  </li>
                </ul>

                <p>If you think your husband or wife might be dead, you don't need to file a divorce petition.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://www.gov.uk/divorce-missing-husband-wife">Apply to end the marriage without filing for divorce</a>
                    <span class="task-list__cost">&pound;365</span>
                  </li>
                </ul>

              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="task-list__group">
          <span class="task-list__number">
            <span class="visuallyhidden">Step</span> 4
          </span>

          <div class="task-list__step js-step">
            <div class="task-list__header js-toggle-panel">
              <h2 class="task-list__title js-step-title">
                Send the court more details about your divorce
              </h2>
            </div>

            <div class="task-list__panel js-panel">
              <p>If the court agrees with your divorce petition, you can apply for a 'decree nisi' and give more information about why the marriage has broken down.</p>
              <ul class="task-list__panel-links--required">
                <li>
                  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/divorce/apply-for-decree-nisi">Why you need a decree nisi</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=154">Fill in the application form</a>
                </li>
              </ul>

              <p>Fill in the form that describes why your marriage has broken down:</p>
              <ul class="task-list__panel-links--options task-list__panel-links--required">
                <li>
                  <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=142">Adultery</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=144">Unreasonable behaviour</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=146">Desertion</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=149">2 years' separation</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=150">5 years' separation</a>
                </li>
              </ul>

              <p>Send the forms to the court.</p>

              <div class="task-list__inner-step task-list__inner-step--optional">
                <p>If your husband or wife doesn't agree to the divorce, you might have to attend a court hearing with a judge.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://www.gov.uk/find-a-legal-adviser">Get legal advice about going to court</a>
                    <span class="task-list__cost">&pound;15,000 to &pound;30,000</span>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="task-list__group">
          <span class="task-list__number">
            <span class="visuallyhidden">Step</span> 5
          </span>

          <div class="task-list__step js-step">
            <div class="task-list__header js-toggle-panel">
              <h2 class="task-list__title js-step-title">
                Finalise your divorce
              </h2>
            </div>

            <div class="task-list__panel js-panel">
              <p>Once you, your husband or wife, and the court all agree, you can apply for a 'decree absolute' to end your marriage. You can do this 6 weeks to 12 months after you receive the conditional order.</p>
              <p>If you want a legally-binding arrangement for dividing money and property you must apply to the court for this before you apply for a decree absolute.</p>
              <ul class="task-list__panel-links--required">
                <li>
                  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/divorce/apply-for-a-decree-absolute">Why you need a decree absolute</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=1114">Fill in the application form</a>
                </li>
              </ul>

              <p>Send the forms to court. Once it's approved, they'll send you and your husband or wife the decree absolute and your divorce will be complete.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
